      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, irregular spots that resemble nibbled patches could indeed be a sign of a disease, such as fungal or bacterial infections, rather than pests. Diseases can cause similar symptoms to pests, like yellowing leaves and brown spots, but they often have a more systemic effect on the plant. Fungal diseases, for example, can create lesions or spots on leaves, while bacterial infections might cause wilting or discoloration. To differentiate between the two, you might want to look for other signs of disease, such as mold or mildew on the leaves or stems, or a general decline in the plant's health. If you suspect a disease, it's best to remove the affected leaves and dispose of them properly to prevent the spread. Additionally, improving air circulation around your plant and avoiding overwatering can help prevent many common plant diseases. Remember, diagnosing plant health issues can sometimes be tricky, so if you're unsure, consulting with a local nursery or plant specialist might be a good idea. Good luck, and may your Monstera thrive despite the challenges!",
